lead_paragraph: LEAD: A moderate earthquake under the San Jacinto Mountains was felt in an 85-mile stretch of southern California Saturday, but there were no reports of damage or injury. The temblor came at 3:16 P.M. and measured 4.3 on the Richter scale of ground motion, a California Institute of Technology spokesman said at Pasadena.
